{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":976,"text":"Khan Academy is most known\nfor its collection of videos,"},{"time":4000,"text":"so before I go any further,"},{"time":6000,"text":"let me show you a little bit of a montage."}]},{"cues":[{"time":9363,"text":"(Video) Salman Khan: So the hypotenuse\nis now going to be five."},{"time":12459,"text":"This animal's fossils are only found\nin this area of South America --"},{"time":15776,"text":"a nice clean band here --"},{"time":17380,"text":"and this part of Africa."},{"time":19593,"text":"We can integrate over the surface,"},{"time":21783,"text":"and the notation\nusually is a capital sigma."},{"time":24648,"text":"National Assembly: They create\nthe Committee of Public Safety,"},{"time":27838,"text":"which sounds like a very nice committee."},{"time":29823,"text":"Notice, this is an aldehyde,\nand it's an alcohol."},{"time":33552,"text":"Start differentiating\ninto effector and memory cells."},{"time":36821,"text":"A galaxy. Hey! There's another galaxy.\nOh, look! There's another galaxy."},{"time":40565,"text":"And for dollars, is their 30 million,"},{"time":43000,"text":"plus the 20 million dollars\nfrom the American manufacturer."},{"time":46063,"text":"If this does not blow your mind,"},{"time":49587,"text":"then you have no emotion."}]},{"cues":[{"time":51618,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":53000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":58539,"text":"(Live) SK: We now have\non the order of 2,200 videos,"},{"time":62544,"text":"covering everything from basic arithmetic,\nall the way to vector calculus,"},{"time":66759,"text":"and some of the stuff\nthat you saw up there."},{"time":69000,"text":"We have a million students\na month using the site,"},{"time":72428,"text":"watching on the order\nof 100 to 200,000 videos a day."},{"time":76000,"text":"But what we're going to talk about in this\nis how we're going to the next level."},{"time":80674,"text":"But before I do that,"},{"time":82000,"text":"I want to talk a little bit\nabout really just how I got started."},{"time":85920,"text":"And some of you all might know,"},{"time":88245,"text":"about five years ago,\nI was an analyst at a hedge fund,"},{"time":91290,"text":"and I was in Boston,"},{"time":93782,"text":"and I was tutoring my cousins\nin New Orleans, remotely."},{"time":96894,"text":"And I started putting\nthe first YouTube videos up,"},{"time":99259,"text":"really just as a kind of nice-to-have,"},{"time":101117,"text":"just kind of a supplement for my cousins,"},{"time":103266,"text":"something that might give them\na refresher or something."}]},{"cues":[{"time":106298,"text":"And as soon as I put those\nfirst YouTube videos up,"},{"time":108962,"text":"something interesting happened."},{"time":110490,"text":"Actually, a bunch of interesting\nthings happened."},{"time":112858,"text":"The first was the feedback\nfrom my cousins."},{"time":115707,"text":"They told me that they preferred\nme on YouTube than in person."}]},{"cues":[{"time":120472,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":127473,"text":"And once you get over\nthe backhanded nature of that,"},{"time":131787,"text":"there was actually something\nvery profound there."},{"time":134119,"text":"They were saying that they preferred\nthe automated version of their cousin"},{"time":137969,"text":"to their cousin."},{"time":139580,"text":"At first it's very unintuitive,"},{"time":141093,"text":"but when you think about it from their\npoint of view, it makes a ton of sense."},{"time":144875,"text":"You have this situation where now\nthey can pause and repeat their cousin,"},{"time":148719,"text":"without feeling\nlike they're wasting my time."},{"time":151767,"text":"If they have to review something"},{"time":154163,"text":"that they should have learned\na couple of weeks ago,"},{"time":156742,"text":"or maybe a couple of years ago,"},{"time":158988,"text":"they don't have to be embarrassed\nand ask their cousin."},{"time":161670,"text":"They can just watch those videos;\nif they're bored, they can go ahead."},{"time":165036,"text":"They can watch at their own time and pace."},{"time":167084,"text":"Probably the least-appreciated aspect\nof this"},{"time":171909,"text":"is the notion that the very first time"},{"time":174504,"text":"that you're trying to get\nyour brain around a new concept,"},{"time":178376,"text":"the very last thing you need"},{"time":180000,"text":"is another human being saying,\n\"Do you understand this?\""},{"time":183194,"text":"And that's what was happening"},{"time":184612,"text":"with the interaction\nwith my cousins before,"},{"time":186731,"text":"and now they can just do it\nin the intimacy of their own room."}]},{"cues":[{"time":193313,"text":"The other thing that happened is --"},{"time":195034,"text":"I put them on YouTube just --"},{"time":198551,"text":"I saw no reason to make it private,"},{"time":200374,"text":"so I let other people watch it,"},{"time":202000,"text":"and then people started stumbling on it,"},{"time":204000,"text":"and I started getting\nsome comments and some letters"},{"time":207522,"text":"and all sorts of feedback"},{"time":209752,"text":"from random people around the world."},{"time":211712,"text":"These are just a few."},{"time":214662,"text":"This is actually from one\nof the original calculus videos."},{"time":218180,"text":"Someone wrote it on YouTube,\nit was a YouTube comment:"},{"time":221285,"text":"\"First time I smiled doing a derivative.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":224000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":226920,"text":"Let's pause here."},{"time":228746,"text":"This person did a derivative,"},{"time":230722,"text":"and then they smiled."}]},{"cues":[{"time":231923,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":233728,"text":"In response to that same comment --"},{"time":235435,"text":"this is on the thread, you can go\non YouTube and look at the comments --"},{"time":238910,"text":"someone else wrote: \"Same thing here."},{"time":240712,"text":"I actually got a natural high\nand a good mood for the entire day,"},{"time":243809,"text":"since I remember seeing\nall of this matrix text in class,"},{"time":248261,"text":"and here I'm all like, 'I know kung fu.'\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":251000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":255285,"text":"We get a lot of feedback\nalong those lines."},{"time":257660,"text":"This clearly was helping people."},{"time":259365,"text":"But then, as the viewership\nkept growing and kept growing,"},{"time":263091,"text":"I started getting letters from people,"},{"time":265686,"text":"and it was starting to become clear"},{"time":267447,"text":"that it was more than just a nice-to-have."},{"time":269553,"text":"This is just an excerpt\nfrom one of those letters:"},{"time":273000,"text":"\"My 12 year-old son has autism,"},{"time":275495,"text":"and has had a terrible time with math."},{"time":277741,"text":"We have tried everything,"},{"time":279000,"text":"viewed everything, bought everything."},{"time":281000,"text":"We stumbled on your video\non decimals, and it got through."},{"time":284709,"text":"Then we went on to the dreaded fractions."},{"time":286717,"text":"Again, he got it."},{"time":287892,"text":"We could not believe it."},{"time":289082,"text":"He is so excited.\""},{"time":291184,"text":"And so you can imagine,"},{"time":292574,"text":"here I was, an analyst at a hedge fund --"},{"time":296732,"text":"it was very strange for me to do\nsomething of social value."}]},{"cues":[{"time":300025,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":302000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":308704,"text":"But I was excited, so I kept going."},{"time":312000,"text":"And then a few other things\nstarted to dawn on me;"},{"time":314722,"text":"that not only would it\nhelp my cousins right now,"},{"time":317214,"text":"or these people who were sending letters,"},{"time":319293,"text":"but that this content will never grow old,"},{"time":322189,"text":"that it could help their kids\nor their grandkids."},{"time":325507,"text":"If Isaac Newton had done\nYouTube videos on calculus,"},{"time":330293,"text":"I wouldn't have to."}]},{"cues":[{"time":331555,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":333364,"text":"Assuming he was good. We don't know."}]},{"cues":[{"time":336000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":338626,"text":"The other thing that happened --\nand even at this point, I said,"},{"time":341690,"text":"\"OK, maybe it's a good supplement.\nIt's good for motivated students."},{"time":344928,"text":"It's good for maybe home-schoolers.\""},{"time":346778,"text":"But I didn't think it would somehow\npenetrate the classroom."},{"time":350077,"text":"Then I started getting\nletters from teachers,"},{"time":352227,"text":"and the teachers would write, saying,"},{"time":354076,"text":"\"We've used your videos\nto flip the classroom."},{"time":356321,"text":"You've given the lectures,\nso now what we do --\""},{"time":358922,"text":"And this could happen in every classroom\nin America tomorrow --"},{"time":362484,"text":"\"what I do is I assign\nthe lectures for homework,"},{"time":365762,"text":"and what used to be homework,"},{"time":367809,"text":"I now have the students\ndoing in the classroom.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":370785,"text":"And I want to pause here --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":373277,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":377894,"text":"I want to pause here, because there's\na couple of interesting things."},{"time":381215,"text":"One, when those teachers are doing that,"},{"time":383440,"text":"there's the obvious benefit --"},{"time":385000,"text":"the benefit that now their students"},{"time":387524,"text":"can enjoy the videos in the way\nthat my cousins did,"},{"time":390070,"text":"they can pause, repeat at their\nown pace, at their own time."},{"time":393500,"text":"But the more interesting thing --\nand this is the unintuitive thing"},{"time":396705,"text":"when you talk about technology\nin the classroom --"},{"time":399107,"text":"by removing the one-size-fits-all\nlecture from the classroom,"},{"time":402017,"text":"and letting students have\na self-paced lecture at home,"},{"time":405041,"text":"then when you go to the classroom,"},{"time":406716,"text":"letting them do work,\nhaving the teacher walk around,"},{"time":409240,"text":"having the peers actually be able\nto interact with each other,"},{"time":412350,"text":"these teachers have used technology\nto humanize the classroom."},{"time":418008,"text":"They took a fundamentally\ndehumanizing experience --"},{"time":420494,"text":"30 kids with their fingers on their lips,"},{"time":423009,"text":"not allowed to interact with each other."},{"time":424987,"text":"A teacher, no matter how good,"},{"time":426503,"text":"has to give this one-size-fits-all\nlecture to 30 students --"},{"time":429836,"text":"blank faces, slightly antagonistic --"},{"time":432223,"text":"and now it's a human experience,"},{"time":433818,"text":"now they're actually\ninteracting with each other."}]},{"cues":[{"time":436151,"text":"So once the Khan Academy --"},{"time":438960,"text":"I quit my job,"},{"time":440136,"text":"and we turned into a real organization --"},{"time":442604,"text":"we're a not-for-profit --"},{"time":444421,"text":"the question is, how do we take this\nto the next level?"},{"time":447539,"text":"How do we take what those teachers\nwere doing to its natural conclusion?"},{"time":451071,"text":"And so, what I'm showing over here,"},{"time":453000,"text":"these are actual exercises"},{"time":455658,"text":"that I started writing for my cousins."},{"time":458000,"text":"The ones I started\nwere much more primitive."},{"time":460120,"text":"This is a more competent version of it."},{"time":463514,"text":"But the paradigm here is, we'll generate\nas many questions as you need,"},{"time":466927,"text":"until you get that concept,\nuntil you get 10 in a row."},{"time":470000,"text":"And the Khan Academy videos are there."},{"time":472000,"text":"You get hints, the actual\nsteps for that problem,"},{"time":474357,"text":"if you don't know how to do it."},{"time":476338,"text":"The paradigm here seems\nlike a very simple thing:"},{"time":478672,"text":"10 in a row, you move on."},{"time":479894,"text":"But it's fundamentally different"},{"time":481498,"text":"than what's happening\nin classrooms right now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":483809,"text":"In a traditional classroom,"},{"time":485735,"text":"you have homework, lecture,\nhomework, lecture,"},{"time":489000,"text":"and then you have a snapshot exam."},{"time":490863,"text":"And that exam, whether you get\na 70 percent, an 80 percent,"},{"time":494544,"text":"a 90 percent or a 95 percent,"},{"time":496013,"text":"the class moves on to the next topic."},{"time":498480,"text":"And even that 95 percent student --"},{"time":500249,"text":"what was the five percent\nthey didn't know?"},{"time":502282,"text":"Maybe they didn't know what happens when\nyou raise something to the zeroth power."},{"time":506127,"text":"Then you build on that\nin the next concept."},{"time":508400,"text":"That's analogous to --\nimagine learning to ride a bicycle."},{"time":511764,"text":"Maybe I give you a lecture ahead of time,"},{"time":514657,"text":"and I give you a bicycle for two weeks,\nthen I come back after two weeks,"},{"time":518594,"text":"and say, \"Well, let's see.\nYou're having trouble taking left turns."},{"time":521768,"text":"You can't quite stop.\nYou're an 80 percent bicyclist.\""},{"time":525029,"text":"So I put a big \"C\" stamp\non your forehead --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":527475,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":528561,"text":"and then I say, \"Here's a unicycle.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":530347,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":531465,"text":"But as ridiculous as that sounds,"},{"time":533324,"text":"that's exactly what's happening\nin our classrooms right now."},{"time":537000,"text":"And the idea is you fast forward"},{"time":539633,"text":"and good students start failing\nalgebra all of the sudden,"},{"time":542643,"text":"and start failing\ncalculus all of the sudden,"},{"time":544971,"text":"despite being smart,\ndespite having good teachers,"},{"time":547353,"text":"and it's usually because they have\nthese Swiss cheese gaps"},{"time":550121,"text":"that kept building\nthroughout their foundation."},{"time":552354,"text":"So our model is: learn math\nthe way you'd learn anything,"},{"time":555956,"text":"like riding a bicycle."},{"time":557326,"text":"Stay on that bicycle.\nFall off that bicycle."},{"time":560421,"text":"Do it as long as necessary,\nuntil you have mastery."},{"time":563476,"text":"The traditional model,"},{"time":565000,"text":"it penalizes you\nfor experimentation and failure,"},{"time":567596,"text":"but it does not expect mastery."},{"time":569643,"text":"We encourage you to experiment.\nWe encourage you to fail."},{"time":572731,"text":"But we do expect mastery."}]},{"cues":[{"time":575921,"text":"This is just another one of the modules."},{"time":577865,"text":"This is trigonometry."},{"time":579309,"text":"This is shifting and reflecting functions."},{"time":582571,"text":"And they all fit together."},{"time":583999,"text":"We have about 90 of these right now."},{"time":585981,"text":"You can go to the site right now,"},{"time":587614,"text":"it's all free,\nnot trying to sell anything."},{"time":589710,"text":"But the general idea is that they all\nfit into this knowledge map."},{"time":592874,"text":"That top node right there,\nthat's literally single-digit addition,"},{"time":596017,"text":"it's like one plus one is equal to two."},{"time":598316,"text":"The paradigm is, once you get\n10 in a row on that,"},{"time":600692,"text":"it keeps forwarding you\nto more and more advanced modules."}]},{"cues":[{"time":603899,"text":"Further down the knowledge map,"},{"time":607002,"text":"we're getting into more\nadvanced arithmetic."},{"time":609273,"text":"Further down, you start getting\ninto pre-algebra and early algebra."},{"time":612470,"text":"Further down, you start getting\ninto algebra one, algebra two,"},{"time":616237,"text":"a little bit of precalculus."},{"time":618142,"text":"And the idea is, from this we can\nactually teach everything --"},{"time":621363,"text":"well, everything that can be taught\nin this type of a framework."},{"time":625229,"text":"So you can imagine -- and this\nis what we are working on --"},{"time":628062,"text":"from this knowledge map, you have\nlogic, you have computer programming,"},{"time":631649,"text":"you have grammar, you have genetics,"},{"time":634173,"text":"all based off of that core of,\nif you know this and that,"},{"time":637356,"text":"now you're ready for this next concept."},{"time":640609,"text":"Now that can work well\nfor an individual learner,"},{"time":642935,"text":"and I encourage you\nto do it with your kids,"},{"time":645091,"text":"but I also encourage everyone\nin the audience to do it yourself."},{"time":648154,"text":"It'll change what happens\nat the dinner table."}]},{"cues":[{"time":650380,"text":"But what we want to do"},{"time":651560,"text":"is use the natural conclusion\nof the flipping of the classroom"},{"time":654662,"text":"that those early teachers\nhad emailed me about."},{"time":657059,"text":"And so what I'm showing you here,"},{"time":658676,"text":"this is data from a pilot\nin the Los Altos school district,"},{"time":661588,"text":"where they took two fifth-grade classes\nand two seventh-grade classes,"},{"time":664928,"text":"and completely gutted\ntheir old math curriculum."},{"time":667203,"text":"These kids aren't using textbooks,\nor getting one-size-fits-all lectures."},{"time":670662,"text":"They're doing Khan Academy, that software,\nfor roughly half of their math class."},{"time":674679,"text":"I want to be clear: we don't view this\nas a complete math education."},{"time":677910,"text":"What it does is -- this is\nwhat's happening in Los Altos --"},{"time":680832,"text":"it frees up time --\nit's the blocking and tackling,"},{"time":683257,"text":"making sure you know how to move\nthrough a system of equations,"},{"time":686257,"text":"and it frees up time\nfor the simulations, for the games,"},{"time":688916,"text":"for the mechanics, for the robot-building,"},{"time":690956,"text":"for the estimating how high\nthat hill is based on its shadow."}]},{"cues":[{"time":693862,"text":"And so the paradigm is\nthe teacher walks in every day,"},{"time":696442,"text":"every kid works at their own pace --"},{"time":698244,"text":"this is actually a live dashboard\nfrom the Los Altos school district --"},{"time":701799,"text":"and they look at this dashboard."},{"time":703394,"text":"Every row is a student."},{"time":705108,"text":"Every column is one of those concepts."},{"time":707000,"text":"Green means the student's\nalready proficient."},{"time":709167,"text":"Blue means they're working\non it -- no need to worry."},{"time":711715,"text":"Red means they're stuck."},{"time":713428,"text":"And what the teacher does\nis literally just say,"},{"time":716697,"text":"\"Let me intervene on the red kids.\""},{"time":718396,"text":"Or even better, \"Let me get\none of the green kids,"},{"time":720785,"text":"who are already proficient\nin that concept,"},{"time":722855,"text":"to be the first line of attack,\nand actually tutor their peer.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":728000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":733625,"text":"Now, I come from a very\ndata-centric reality,"},{"time":737000,"text":"so we don't want that teacher\nto even go and intervene"},{"time":739763,"text":"and have to ask the kid awkward questions:"},{"time":741833,"text":"\"What don't you understand? What do\nyou understand?\" and all the rest."},{"time":745167,"text":"So our paradigm is to arm teachers\nwith as much data as possible --"},{"time":748426,"text":"data that, in any other\nfield, is expected,"},{"time":750500,"text":"in finance, marketing, manufacturing --"},{"time":752563,"text":"so the teachers can diagnose\nwhat's wrong with the students"},{"time":755384,"text":"so they can make their interaction\nas productive as possible."},{"time":758296,"text":"Now teachers know exactly\nwhat the students have been up to,"},{"time":761154,"text":"how long they've spent each day,\nwhat videos they've watched,"},{"time":764063,"text":"when did they pause the videos,\nwhat did they stop watching,"},{"time":766921,"text":"what exercises are they using,\nwhat have they focused on?"},{"time":769668,"text":"The outer circle shows\nwhat exercises they were focused on."},{"time":772565,"text":"The inner circle shows\nthe videos they're focused on."},{"time":775881,"text":"The data gets pretty granular,"},{"time":777342,"text":"so you can see the exact problems\nthe student got right or wrong."},{"time":780453,"text":"Red is wrong, blue is right."},{"time":782206,"text":"The leftmost question is the first one\nthe student attempted."},{"time":785204,"text":"They watched the video over there."},{"time":786870,"text":"And you can see, eventually\nthey were able to get 10 in a row."},{"time":789838,"text":"It's almost like you can see them\nlearning over those last 10 problems."},{"time":793217,"text":"They also got faster -- the height\nis how long it took them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":798221,"text":"When you talk about self-paced learning,\nit makes sense for everyone --"},{"time":802744,"text":"in education-speak,\n\"differentiated learning\" --"},{"time":805189,"text":"but it's kind of crazy, what happens\nwhen you see it in a classroom."},{"time":808895,"text":"Because every time we've done this,\nin every classroom we've done,"},{"time":813363,"text":"over and over again,\nif you go five days into it,"},{"time":815711,"text":"there's a group of kids who've raced ahead"},{"time":817748,"text":"and a group who are a little bit slower."},{"time":819685,"text":"In a traditional model,\nin a snapshot assessment,"},{"time":822112,"text":"you say, \"These are the gifted kids,\nthese are the slow kids."},{"time":825048,"text":"Maybe they should be tracked differently."},{"time":827040,"text":"Maybe we should put them\nin different classes.\""},{"time":829294,"text":"But when you let students\nwork at their own pace --"},{"time":831722,"text":"we see it over and over again --"},{"time":833347,"text":"you see students who took\na little bit extra time"},{"time":835796,"text":"on one concept or the other,"},{"time":837671,"text":"but once they get through that concept,"},{"time":839891,"text":"they just race ahead."},{"time":841263,"text":"And so the same kids that you\nthought were slow six weeks ago,"},{"time":844659,"text":"you now would think are gifted."},{"time":846342,"text":"And we're seeing it over and over again."},{"time":848358,"text":"It makes you really wonder"},{"time":850167,"text":"how much all of the labels maybe\na lot of us have benefited from"},{"time":853490,"text":"were really just due\nto a coincidence of time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":859227,"text":"Now as valuable as something like this is\nin a district like Los Altos,"},{"time":864283,"text":"our goal is to use technology"},{"time":866000,"text":"to humanize, not just in Los Altos,\nbut on a global scale,"},{"time":869000,"text":"what's happening in education."},{"time":871527,"text":"And that brings up an interesting point."},{"time":873852,"text":"A lot of the effort\nin humanizing the classroom"},{"time":876606,"text":"is focused on student-to-teacher ratios."},{"time":879550,"text":"In our mind, the relevant metric is:"},{"time":882073,"text":"student-to-valuable-human-time-\nwith-the-teacher ratio."},{"time":885999,"text":"So in a traditional model,\nmost of the teacher's time"},{"time":888548,"text":"is spent doing lectures\nand grading and whatnot."},{"time":890944,"text":"Maybe five percent of their time\nis sitting next to students"},{"time":893864,"text":"and working with them."},{"time":895048,"text":"Now, 100 percent of their time is."},{"time":897079,"text":"So once again, using technology,\nnot just flipping the classroom,"},{"time":900373,"text":"you're humanizing\nthe classroom, I'd argue,"},{"time":902755,"text":"by a factor of five or 10."}]},{"cues":[{"time":905396,"text":"As valuable as that is in Los Altos,"},{"time":907150,"text":"imagine what it does to the adult learner,"},{"time":909215,"text":"who's embarrassed to go back\nand learn stuff"},{"time":911302,"text":"they should have known\nbefore going back to college."},{"time":913778,"text":"Imagine what it does\nto a street kid in Calcutta,"},{"time":919735,"text":"who has to help his family during the day,"},{"time":922501,"text":"and that's the reason\nhe or she can't go to school."},{"time":924931,"text":"Now they can spend two hours\na day and remediate,"},{"time":927438,"text":"or get up to speed\nand not feel embarrassed"},{"time":929787,"text":"about what they do or don't know."},{"time":932406,"text":"Now imagine what happens where --"},{"time":934058,"text":"we talked about the peers\nteaching each other"},{"time":936993,"text":"inside of a classroom."},{"time":938826,"text":"But this is all one system."},{"time":940580,"text":"There's no reason why you can't\nhave that peer-to-peer tutoring"},{"time":943906,"text":"beyond that one classroom."},{"time":946000,"text":"Imagine what happens\nif that student in Calcutta"},{"time":949000,"text":"all of the sudden can tutor your son,"},{"time":951192,"text":"or your son can tutor\nthat kid in Calcutta."},{"time":954121,"text":"And I think what you'll see emerging"},{"time":956000,"text":"is this notion of a global\none-world classroom."},{"time":962602,"text":"And that's essentially\nwhat we're trying to build."}]},{"cues":[{"time":966562,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":967738,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":975960,"text":"Bill Gates: I'll ask about two\nor three questions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":978420,"text":"Salman Khan: Oh, OK."}]},{"cues":[{"time":980166,"text":"(Applause continues)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1007711,"text":"(Applause ends)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1009084,"text":"BG: I've seen some things\nyou're doing in the system,"},{"time":1012044,"text":"that have to do with motivation\nand feedback --"},{"time":1014505,"text":"energy points, merit badges."},{"time":1017000,"text":"Tell me what you're thinking there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1019055,"text":"SK: Oh yeah. No, we have\nan awesome team working on it."},{"time":1021675,"text":"I have to be clear,\nit's not just me anymore."},{"time":1023802,"text":"I'm still doing all the videos,"},{"time":1025311,"text":"but we have a rock-star team\ndoing the software."},{"time":1027637,"text":"We've put a bunch of game mechanics\nin there, where you get badges,"},{"time":1030820,"text":"we're going to start having leader boards\nby area, you get points."},{"time":1034103,"text":"It's actually been pretty interesting."},{"time":1035953,"text":"Just the wording of the badging,"},{"time":1037536,"text":"or how many points you get\nfor doing something,"},{"time":1039767,"text":"we see on a system-wide basis,"},{"time":1041428,"text":"like tens of thousands\nof fifth-graders or sixth-graders"},{"time":1044090,"text":"going one direction or another,\ndepending what badge you give them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1047289,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1049376,"text":"BG: And the collaboration\nyou're doing with Los Altos,"},{"time":1052000,"text":"how did that come about?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1054201,"text":"SK: Los Altos, it was kind of crazy."},{"time":1057264,"text":"Once again, I didn't expect it\nto be used in classrooms."},{"time":1060097,"text":"Someone from their board came and said,"},{"time":1062000,"text":"\"What would you do if you had\ncarte Blanche in a classroom?\""},{"time":1064851,"text":"I said, \"Well, every student\nwould work at their own pace,"},{"time":1067891,"text":"on something like this,\nwe'd give a dashboard.\""},{"time":1070112,"text":"They said, \"This is kind of radical.\nWe have to think about it.\""},{"time":1073335,"text":"Me and the rest of the team were like,\n\"They're never going to want to do this.\""},{"time":1077161,"text":"But literally the next day they were like,\n\"Can you start in two weeks?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1080606,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1082081,"text":"BG: So fifth-grade math\nis where that's going on right now?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1085002,"text":"SK: It's two fifth-grade classes\nand two seventh-grade classes."},{"time":1088025,"text":"They're doing it at the district level."},{"time":1089915,"text":"I think what they're excited about\nis they can follow these kids,"},{"time":1093011,"text":"not only in school; on Christmas,\nwe saw some of the kids were doing it."},{"time":1096448,"text":"We can track everything, track them\nas they go through the entire district."},{"time":1100000,"text":"Through the summers, as they go\nfrom one teacher to the next,"},{"time":1102952,"text":"you have this continuity of data that\neven at the district level, they can see."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1106776,"text":"BG: So some of those views we saw\nwere for the teacher"},{"time":1110000,"text":"to go in and track actually\nwhat's going on with those kids."},{"time":1113715,"text":"So you're getting feedback\non those teacher views"},{"time":1116065,"text":"to see what they think they need?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1117802,"text":"SK: Oh yeah. Most of those\nwere specs by the teachers."},{"time":1122182,"text":"We made some of those for students\nso they could see their data,"},{"time":1125216,"text":"but we have a very tight design loop\nwith the teachers themselves."},{"time":1128352,"text":"And they're saying,\n\"Hey, this is nice, but --\""},{"time":1130600,"text":"Like that focus graph,\na lot of the teachers said,"},{"time":1133013,"text":"\"I have a feeling a lot of the kids\nare jumping around"},{"time":1135577,"text":"and not focusing on one topic.\""},{"time":1137203,"text":"So we made that focus diagram."},{"time":1138700,"text":"So it's all been teacher-driven.\nIt's been pretty crazy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1141364,"text":"BG: Is this ready for prime time?"},{"time":1142961,"text":"Do you think a lot of classes next school\nyear should try this thing out?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1147339,"text":"SK: Yeah, it's ready."},{"time":1148521,"text":"We've got a million people\non the site already,"},{"time":1151263,"text":"so we can handle a few more."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1154219,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1156000,"text":"No, no reason why it really can't happen"},{"time":1158000,"text":"in every classroom in America tomorrow."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1160634,"text":"BG: And the vision of the tutoring thing."},{"time":1163138,"text":"The idea there is,\nif I'm confused about a topic,"},{"time":1166000,"text":"somehow right in the user interface,"},{"time":1168176,"text":"I'd find people who are volunteering,"},{"time":1170336,"text":"maybe see their reputation,"},{"time":1172098,"text":"and I could schedule and connect up\nwith those people?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1175299,"text":"SK: Absolutely. And this is something\nI recommend everyone in this audience do."},{"time":1179072,"text":"Those dashboards the teachers have,\nyou can go log in right now"},{"time":1182158,"text":"and you can essentially become a coach"},{"time":1184000,"text":"for your kids, your nephews, your cousins,"},{"time":1187000,"text":"or maybe some kids\nat the Boys and Girls Club."},{"time":1189853,"text":"And yeah, you can start\nbecoming a mentor, a tutor,"},{"time":1192409,"text":"really immediately."},{"time":1193905,"text":"But yeah, it's all there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1195890,"text":"BG: Well, it's amazing."},{"time":1197072,"text":"I think you just got a glimpse\nof the future of education."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1200158,"text":"BG: Thank you.\nSK: Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1202000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}